PYTHON
Install Anaconda

ANACONDA
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-the-anaconda-python-distribution-on-ubuntu-16-04

-Copy the download link anaconda - I only downloaded the 3.6 version
https://www.anaconda.com/download/#linux

-The link should look like this:
https://repo.continuum.io/archive/Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

-Navigate to the /tmp directory
cd /tmp

-Use curl to download the package
curl -O https://repo.continuum.io/archive/Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

-Verify the SHA-526 checksum
sha256sum Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

-The result should look like something like this:
55e4db1919f49c92d5abbf27a4be5986ae157f074bf9f8238963cd4582a4068a  Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

-Run the script
bash Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh

-press RETURN/ENTER to move through the license agreement
-Answer yes to the license agreement

-When asked about location, press RETURN/ENTER to install in the home directory

-When asked if the installer should prepend the PATH, type yes

-activate the installation
source ~/.bashrc

OR

-open a new terminal window

-update conda
conda update conda

-update anaconda
conda update anaconda

-open anaconda navigator
anaconda-navigator

Done
